<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 65px">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg" class="image" title="Arabic albayancalligraphy.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg/65px-Arabic_albayancalligraphy.svg.png" width="65" height="29" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle"><b>This article contains <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic text</a>, written from right to left in a cursive style with some letters joined.</b> Without proper <a href="/wiki/Help:Arabic" title="Help:Arabic">rendering support</a>, you may see unjoined Arabic letters written left-to-right, instead of right-to-left or other symbols instead of <a href="/wiki/Arabic_script" title="Arabic script" class="mw-redirect">Arabic script</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Arabic</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Semitic_languages" title="Semitic languages">Semitic</a> language. See <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" title="Arabic language">Arabic language</a> for more information on the language in general. This article describes the grammar of <a href="/wiki/Classical_Arabic" title="Classical Arabic">Classical Arabic</a> and <a href="/wiki/Modern_Standard_Arabic" title="Modern Standard Arabic">Modern Standard Arabic</a> - the Arabic grammar (<b>نحو عربي</b> <i>naḥw ʻarabī</i> or <b>قواعد اللغة العربية</b> <i>qawāʻidu 'l-luġati 'lʻarabiyyah</i>).</p>
